# 1Password env-file template — `op run --env-file=.env.op -- <cmd>` resolves
# the op:// references to actual secret values and injects them as env vars
# for the wrapped command. The values never appear in shell scrollback,
# history, or the terminal session of the agent invoking `op run`.
#
# This file is committed (it contains references, not secrets). Anyone with
# read access to the Goldberry Grove - Admin vault's GoldberryGrove Infra
# item gets the values; anyone without it gets `op` errors and nothing leaks.
#
# Prerequisites in 1Password (Goldberry Grove - Admin → GoldberryGrove Infra):
#   - do_token                          (concealed) — DO API token, spaces + spaces_key scopes
#   - github_token                      (concealed) — GitHub PAT, Actions:Secrets RW on odoocker
#   - spaces_bootstrap_access_key_id    (concealed) — Spaces key, All Buckets / Full Access.
#                                                      Used by the DO TF provider for bucket ops
#                                                      (long-lived plumbing — not pushed to workflows)
#   - spaces_bootstrap_secret_key       (concealed) — companion secret to the above

TF_VAR_do_token=op://Goldberry Grove - Admin/GoldberryGrove Infra/do_token
TF_VAR_github_token=op://Goldberry Grove - Admin/GoldberryGrove Infra/github_token
TF_VAR_spaces_bootstrap_access_key_id=op://Goldberry Grove - Admin/GoldberryGrove Infra/spaces_bootstrap_access_key_id
TF_VAR_spaces_bootstrap_secret_key=op://Goldberry Grove - Admin/GoldberryGrove Infra/spaces_bootstrap_secret_key
